                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.51/297: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-11T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 11, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received June 12, 11.13 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s June 5, 6 p.m. This afternoon President Cabrera requested me to
                    inform the Department that he accepts with pleasure the appointment of Professor
                    Kemmerer and that the salary arrangement and that regarding the time to be
                    devoted to the work are satisfactory. He further stated that every assistance
                    will be given Professor Kemmerer.</p>
                <p>The Banco Americano has been given 6,000,000 pesos and expects 4,000,000 more.
                    Four banks dominated by the Government have drawn up petition requesting
                    issuance of the 60,000,000 under greatly modified version of decree number 1003.
                    Nevertheless President Cabrera again assured me this afternoon this issue will
                    be withheld.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
